        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3136226?u=5d5e6a3ec492970073606b81b1e1f7a307dd1175&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><h2 dir=\"auto\">Request for Mozilla Position on an Emerging Web Specification</h2>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>Specification title: Viewport Capture</li>\n<li>Specification URL: <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/mediacapture-viewport/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.w3.org/TR/mediacapture-viewport/</a></li>\n<li>Bugzilla URL (optional): <a href=\"https://bugzil.la/1813091\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://bugzil.la/1813091</a></li>\n<li>Mozillians who can provide input (optional): <a class=\"user-mention notranslate\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/jan-ivar/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/jan-ivar\">@jan-ivar</a>, <a class=\"user-mention notranslate\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/martinthomson/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/martinthomson\">@martinthomson</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Other information</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">This API (<a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/mediacapture-viewport/#dom-mediadevices-getviewportmedia\" rel=\"nofollow\">getViewportMedia</a>) lets site-isolated webpages screen-capture themselves, eliminating the need for a content picker. Target use cases are client-side \"record meeting\" features, as well as integrating video conferencing into slideware applications.</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">It contains privacy features absent in <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/screen-capture/#dom-mediadevices-getdisplaymedia\" rel=\"nofollow\">getDisplayMedia()</a> and <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"1825415905\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mozilla/standards-positions/issues/857\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/mozilla/standards-positions/issues/857/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/mozilla/standards-positions/issues/857\">#857</a>, to address <a href=\"https://blog.mozilla.org/webrtc/share-browser-windows-entire-screen-sites-trust/\" rel=\"nofollow\">privacy concerns inherent in self-capture</a>:</p>\n<ol dir=\"auto\">\n<li>The API is limited to <a href=\"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/webappapis.html#concept-settings-object-cross-origin-isolated-capability\" rel=\"nofollow\">cross-origin isolated</a> webpages.</li>\n<li>The API is opt-in through <code class=\"notranslate\">Document-Policy: viewport-capture</code> and <code class=\"notranslate\">Require-Document-Policy: viewport-capture</code></li>\n</ol>",
