        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/153264?u=8928381dcceca8b3cd411e76d118b03da5e74ed9&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><h2 dir=\"auto\">Request for Mozilla Position on an Emerging Web Specification</h2>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>Specification title: WebAuthn</li>\n<li>Specification or proposal URL (if available): <a href=\"https://w3c.github.io/webauthn/#publickey-credentials-create-feature\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://w3c.github.io/webauthn/#publickey-credentials-create-feature</a></li>\n<li>Explainer URL (if available):</li>\n<li>Proposal author(s) (<code class=\"notranslate\">@</code>-mention GitHub accounts): <a class=\"user-mention notranslate\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/users/stephenmcgruer/hovercard\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/stephenmcgruer\">@stephenmcgruer</a></li>\n<li>Caniuse.com URL (optional):</li>\n<li>Bugzilla URL (optional):</li>\n<li>Mozillians who can provide input (optional):</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Other information</h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Hello Mozilla friends :)</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">I'm requested a formal standards position on the ability to create a credential in a cross-origin iframe in WebAuthn. This was added to the spec in <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"1372146083\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/w3c/webauthn/issues/1801\" data-hovercard-type=\"pull_request\" data-hovercard-url=\"/w3c/webauthn/pull/1801/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/w3c/webauthn/pull/1801\">w3c/webauthn#1801</a>, after having been discussed in <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"954246546\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/w3c/webauthn/issues/1656\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/w3c/webauthn/issues/1656/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/w3c/webauthn/issues/1656\">w3c/webauthn#1656</a> as well as in WebAuthn Working Group meetings.</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">This feature allows web developers to create WebAuthn credentials (that is, \"publickey\" credentials, aka passkeys) in cross-origin iframes. This will allow developers to create passkeys in embedded scenarios, such as after an identity step-up flow where the Relying Party is providing a federated identity experience. Two conditions are required for this new ability, for security reasons:</p>\n<ol dir=\"auto\">\n<li>The iframe has a publickey-credentials-create-feature permission policy.</li>\n<li>The iframe has transient user activation.</li>\n</ol>",
            "url": "https://github.com/mozilla/standards-positions/issues/964",
            "title": "WebAuthn: Allow for credential creation in a cross-origin iframe",
